 THREE people died at a birthday party after about 30kg of dry ice was tipped into a pool. The ice was meant to create special effects. The party on Friday was to mark the birthday of Ekaterina Didenko, a popular Instagram influencer focusing on pharmaceutical products with more than a million followers. Didenko’s husband Valentin died in hospital, the TASS news agency reported. Four other people sustained chemical burns and poisoning. The RIA Novosti news agency said the victims had jumped into the pool after the ice had been tipped into the water and suffered chemical reactions. – NEWS24